rity (junub). The Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25536,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/04\/recommendation-wudu-every-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25528,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Performing ablution for every prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 4, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would perform ablution at the time of every prayer. 'Amr said, \u201cHow would you do so?\u201d Anas said, \u201cIt is permissible for one of us to maintain ablution for multiple prayers, as long as he does not become\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13448,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/07\/method-ghusl-junub\/","url_meta":{"origin":25528,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ghusl: Performing ritual bath for major impurity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 7, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, took a ritual bath for major impurity, he began by washing his hands, then he would perform an ablution as if for prayer. Then, he would put his fingers in the water and wash the roots of his hair\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":293,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/12\/31\/miracle-prophet-water\/","url_meta":{"origin":25528,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Miracles: The Prophet&#8217;s miracle of providing water","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 31, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: I saw the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, during the afternoon prayer and people were asking for water to perform ablution, but they could not find it. Some water was brought to the Prophet and he placed his hand in the vessel\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25505,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/beginning-deeds-yamin-yameen\/","url_meta":{"origin":25528,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Mindfulness: Beginning actions with the right side","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, liked to begin on his right side when putting on his shoes, combing his hair, performing his ablution, and in all of his affairs. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 168, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 268 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25583,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/10\/wudu-nawm-junub\/","url_meta":{"origin":25528,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Perform ablution if sleeping with major impurity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 10, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: If the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, intended to sleep while in a state of major ritual impurity, he would perform ablution before he slept. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 282, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 305 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25528","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25528"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25528\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=25528"}],"wp: